                Job Post Details

                Angular Developer - job post

                Iconvergence
                Remote
                $48.77 - $52.75 an hour - Full-time, Contract

                Profile insights

                Find out how your skills align with the job description

                Skills

                Do you have experience in UI design systems?
                &nbsp;

                Job details

                Pay

                • $48.77 - $52.75 an hour

                Job type

                • Contract
                • Full-time

                Shift and schedule

                • 8 hour shift
                • Monday to Friday

                Work setting

                • Remote
                &nbsp;

                Full job description

                Responsibilities:

                Lead the design and development of scalable, modular, and maintainable
                Angular components.
                Collaborate with UX/UI designers to implement responsive,
                user-friendly interfaces.
                Mentor and guide junior developers through code reviews, best
                practices, and technical discussions.
                Work with backend teams to integrate RESTful APIs and ensure smooth data flow.
                Optimize applications for speed and performance across devices and browsers.
                Identify and resolve technical issues, bugs, and performance bottlenecks.
                Maintain and improve existing codebase, refactoring where necessary.
                Stay current with the latest Angular and front-end development trends.

                Qualifications:

                5+ years of professional front-end development experience.
                3+ years specifically working with Angular (v8 or later).
                Strong knowledge of TypeScript, JavaScript (ES6+), HTML5, and CSS3.
                Experience with RxJS, NgRx or other state management libraries.
                Proficient in RESTful API integration and handling asynchronous operations.
                Strong understanding of component architecture, lazy loading, and
                module bundling.
                Familiarity with testing frameworks such as Jasmine, Karma, or Cypress.
                Experience with Git and Agile development processes (Scrum/Kanban).
                Solid problem-solving and communication skills.

                Preferred Qualifications:

                Experience with backend integration (Node.js, .NET, or Java is a plus).
                Knowledge of SAP Hybris (Commerce Cloud) and its integration with
                front-end applications is a strong plus.
                Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines and containerized environments
                (Docker, Kubernetes).
                Understanding of accessibility (WCAG) and internationalization best practices.
                Contributions to open-source Angular projects or a personal GitHub portfolio.

                Job Types: Full-time, Contract

                Pay: $48.77 - $52.75 per hour

                Schedule:

                • 8 hour shift
                • Monday to Friday

                Work Location: Remote
